WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.500 --> 00:00:09.230
Remove the scales and cut the head off the sardines. 

00:00:10.430 --> 00:00:17.700
Remove the guts, thoroughly wash with water, and wipe dry. 

00:00:19.070 --> 00:00:29.300
Work your fingers along the belly to open up the fish and separate the spine from the flesh.

00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:38.630
Halve the myoga lengthwise and blanch in boiling water. 

00:00:39.670 --> 00:00:52.630
Mix the vinegar and the sugar, add the freshly cooked myoga, and marinate in a plastic bag for about 20 minutes. 

00:00:53.830 --> 00:01:04.300
Mix the sake, the sugar, the mirin, the soy sauce and the ginger juice.

00:01:05.670 --> 00:01:09.970
Coat the sardines in the flour. 

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:29.300
Heat the oil in a non-stick frying pan, fry both sides of the sardines, and remove them from the pan. 

00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:47.500
Put the mixture into the frying pan and reduce some of the liquid. Return the sardines to the pan and cover with the sauce. 

